title: For Sale:  Armalite AR180B Rifle
postcontent:
Up for sale is an Armalite AR180B in good condition.
The AR180 was designed by Eugene Stoner about a decade after he designed the AR-15 and after Armalite sold the design to Colt. It was designed as an easy to manufacture gas-piston rifle that could be produced in less industrial countries more readily than the AR-15 could. Trouble was, around this time (late 60s/early 70s) the US Government was giving everybody who hated commies crateloads of M16s, and so the AR180 never really took off. Later rifles such as the SA80 and G36 would essential copy the simple gas piston action of the AR180 to great effect. Armalite reissued the rifle in the late 90s/early 00s with a new polymer lower reciever, greater AR-15 parts commonality, and the ability to use standard USGI magazines, as well as minor changes like a different charging handle and removing the dust cover. This is the AR180B version complete with the polymer lower.
If you didn't feel like reading that history lesson paragraph, its a well designed rifle with some history. While it hasn't been made for years, Armalite still offers pretty much all of the internal parts on their webstore should you need a replacement.
Rifle is in good condition, less than 500 rounds fired. Only real blemish is a little bit of brass scoring in the star chamber from a doublefeed, which brings me to my second point: Rifle DOES NOT work with any generation of Pmags, you have to use steel GI mags of some sort. It might feed with Pmags but it won't hold the bolt open after the last round. If you need steel mags let me know, I have some PSA mags lying around.
I am not in a hurry to sell, so the rifle is priced accordingly. At the time of this posting there isn't a single AR180B on Gunbroker for less than 700 dollars, mostly because they haven't been manufactured in over a decade now. By buying this rifle you're basically saving me the hassle of posting it up on Gunbroker and shipping through an FFL.
Willing to meet anywhere within reason. Trades I would be interested in are any Bushmaster/Colt style AR15 with a carry handle upper, M4 or M16A2 style, any auto tactical shotguns, Scout style rifles, or lever action hunting rifles.
